33// This file implements draft-irtf-cfrg-hpke-08.
34
35#define MAX_SEED_LEN X25519_PRIVATE_KEY_LEN
36#define MAX_SHARED_SECRET_LEN SHA256_DIGEST_LENGTH
37
38struct evp_hpke_kem_st {
39 uint16_t id;
40 size_t public_key_len;
41 size_t seed_len;
42 int (*init_key)(EVP_HPKE_KEY *key, const EVP_HPKE_KEM *kem,
43 const uint8_t *priv_key, size_t priv_key_len);
44 int (*encap_with_seed)(const EVP_HPKE_KEM *kem, uint8_t *out_shared_secret,
45 size_t *out_shared_secret_len, uint8_t *out_enc,
46 size_t *out_enc_len, size_t max_enc,
47 const uint8_t *peer_public_key,
48 size_t peer_public_key_len, const uint8_t *seed,
49 size_t seed_len);
50 int (*decap)(const EVP_HPKE_KEY *key, uint8_t *out_shared_secret,
51 size_t *out_shared_secret_len, const uint8_t *enc,
52 size_t enc_len);
53};
54
55struct evp_hpke_kdf_st {
56 uint16_t id;
57 // We only support HKDF-based KDFs.
58 const EVP_MD *(*hkdf_md_func)(void);
59};
60
61struct evp_hpke_aead_st {
62 uint16_t id;
63 const EVP_AEAD *(*aead_func)(void);
64};

67// Low-level labeled KDF functions.
68
69static const char kHpkeVersionId[] = "HPKE-v1";
70
71static int add_label_string(CBB *cbb, const char *label) {
72 return CBB_add_bytes(cbb, (const uint8_t *)label, strlen(label));
73}
74
75static int hpke_labeled_extract(const EVP_MD *hkdf_md, uint8_t *out_key,
76 size_t *out_len, const uint8_t *salt,
77 size_t salt_len, const uint8_t *suite_id,
78 size_t suite_id_len, const char *label,
79 const uint8_t *ikm, size_t ikm_len) {
80 // labeledIKM = concat("HPKE-v1", suite_id, label, IKM)
81 CBB labeled_ikm;
82 int ok = CBB_init(&labeled_ikm, 0) &&
83 add_label_string(&labeled_ikm, kHpkeVersionId) &&
84 CBB_add_bytes(&labeled_ikm, suite_id, suite_id_len) &&
85 add_label_string(&labeled_ikm, label) &&
86 CBB_add_bytes(&labeled_ikm, ikm, ikm_len) &&
87 HKDF_extract(out_key, out_len, hkdf_md, CBB_data(&labeled_ikm),
88 CBB_len(&labeled_ikm), salt, salt_len);
89 CBB_cleanup(&labeled_ikm);
90 return ok;
91}
92
93static int hpke_labeled_expand(const EVP_MD *hkdf_md, uint8_t *out_key,
94 size_t out_len, const uint8_t *prk,
95 size_t prk_len, const uint8_t *suite_id,
96 size_t suite_id_len, const char *label,
97 const uint8_t *info, size_t info_len) {
98 // labeledInfo = concat(I2OSP(L, 2), "HPKE-v1", suite_id, label, info)
99 CBB labeled_info;
100 int ok = CBB_init(&labeled_info, 0) &&
101 CBB_add_u16(&labeled_info, out_len) &&
102 add_label_string(&labeled_info, kHpkeVersionId) &&
103 CBB_add_bytes(&labeled_info, suite_id, suite_id_len) &&
104 add_label_string(&labeled_info, label) &&
105 CBB_add_bytes(&labeled_info, info, info_len) &&
106 HKDF_expand(out_key, out_len, hkdf_md, prk, prk_len,
107 CBB_data(&labeled_info), CBB_len(&labeled_info));
108 CBB_cleanup(&labeled_info);
109 return ok;
110}
111
112
113// KEM implementations.
114
115// dhkem_extract_and_expand implements the ExtractAndExpand operation in the
116// DHKEM construction. See section 4.1 of draft-irtf-cfrg-hpke-08.
117static int dhkem_extract_and_expand(uint16_t kem_id, const EVP_MD *hkdf_md,
118 uint8_t *out_key, size_t out_len,
119 const uint8_t *dh, size_t dh_len,
120 const uint8_t *kem_context,
121 size_t kem_context_len) {
122 // concat("KEM", I2OSP(kem_id, 2))
123 uint8_t suite_id[5] = {'K', 'E', 'M', kem_id >> 8, kem_id & 0xff};
124 uint8_t prk[EVP_MAX_MD_SIZE];
125 size_t prk_len;
126 return hpke_labeled_extract(hkdf_md, prk, &prk_len, NULL, 0, suite_id,
127 sizeof(suite_id), "eae_prk", dh, dh_len) &&
128 hpke_labeled_expand(hkdf_md, out_key, out_len, prk, prk_len, suite_id,
129 sizeof(suite_id), "shared_secret", kem_context,
130 kem_context_len);
131}
132
133static int x25519_init_key(EVP_HPKE_KEY *key, const EVP_HPKE_KEM *kem,
134 const uint8_t *priv_key, size_t priv_key_len) {
135 if (priv_key_len != X25519_PRIVATE_KEY_LEN) {
136 OPENSSL_PUT_ERROR(EVP, EVP_R_DECODE_ERROR);
137 return 0;
138 }
139
140 OPENSSL_memcpy(key->private_key, priv_key, priv_key_len);
141 X25519_public_from_private(key->public_key, priv_key);
142 return 1;
143}
144
145static int x25519_encap_with_seed(
146 const EVP_HPKE_KEM *kem, uint8_t *out_shared_secret,
147 size_t *out_shared_secret_len, uint8_t *out_enc, size_t *out_enc_len,
148 size_t max_enc, const uint8_t *peer_public_key, size_t peer_public_key_len,
149 const uint8_t *seed, size_t seed_len) {
150 if (max_enc < X25519_PUBLIC_VALUE_LEN) {
151 OPENSSL_PUT_ERROR(EVP, EVP_R_INVALID_BUFFER_SIZE);
152 return 0;
153 }
154 if (seed_len != X25519_PRIVATE_KEY_LEN) {
155 OPENSSL_PUT_ERROR(EVP, EVP_R_DECODE_ERROR);
156 return 0;
157 }
158 X25519_public_from_private(out_enc, seed);
159
160 uint8_t dh[X25519_SHARED_KEY_LEN];
161 if (peer_public_key_len != X25519_PUBLIC_VALUE_LEN ||
162 !X25519(dh, seed, peer_public_key)) {
163 OPENSSL_PUT_ERROR(EVP, EVP_R_INVALID_PEER_KEY);
164 return 0;
165 }
166
167 uint8_t kem_context[2 * X25519_PUBLIC_VALUE_LEN];
168 OPENSSL_memcpy(kem_context, out_enc, X25519_PUBLIC_VALUE_LEN);
169 OPENSSL_memcpy(kem_context + X25519_PUBLIC_VALUE_LEN, peer_public_key,
170 X25519_PUBLIC_VALUE_LEN);
171 if (!dhkem_extract_and_expand(kem->id, EVP_sha256(), out_shared_secret,
172 SHA256_DIGEST_LENGTH, dh, sizeof(dh),
173 kem_context, sizeof(kem_context))) {
174 return 0;
175 }
176
177 *out_enc_len = X25519_PUBLIC_VALUE_LEN;
178 *out_shared_secret_len = SHA256_DIGEST_LENGTH;
179 return 1;
180}
181
182static int x25519_decap(const EVP_HPKE_KEY *key, uint8_t *out_shared_secret,
183 size_t *out_shared_secret_len, const uint8_t *enc,
184 size_t enc_len) {
185 uint8_t dh[X25519_SHARED_KEY_LEN];
186 if (enc_len != X25519_PUBLIC_VALUE_LEN ||
187 !X25519(dh, key->private_key, enc)) {
188 OPENSSL_PUT_ERROR(EVP, EVP_R_INVALID_PEER_KEY);
189 return 0;
190 }
191
192 uint8_t kem_context[2 * X25519_PUBLIC_VALUE_LEN];
193 OPENSSL_memcpy(kem_context, enc, X25519_PUBLIC_VALUE_LEN);
194 OPENSSL_memcpy(kem_context + X25519_PUBLIC_VALUE_LEN, key->public_key,
195 X25519_PUBLIC_VALUE_LEN);
196 if (!dhkem_extract_and_expand(key->kem->id, EVP_sha256(), out_shared_secret,
197 SHA256_DIGEST_LENGTH, dh, sizeof(dh),
198 kem_context, sizeof(kem_context))) {
199 return 0;
200 }
201
202 *out_shared_secret_len = SHA256_DIGEST_LENGTH;
203 return 1;
204}

206const EVP_HPKE_KEM *EVP_hpke_x25519_hkdf_sha256(void) {
207 static const EVP_HPKE_KEM kKEM = {
208 /*id=*/EVP_HPKE_DHKEM_X25519_HKDF_SHA256,
209 /*public_key_len=*/X25519_PUBLIC_VALUE_LEN,
210 /*seed_len=*/X25519_PRIVATE_KEY_LEN,
211 x25519_init_key,
212 x25519_encap_with_seed,
213 x25519_decap,
214 };
215 return &kKEM;
216}

220void EVP_HPKE_KEY_zero(EVP_HPKE_KEY *key) {
221 OPENSSL_memset(key, 0, sizeof(EVP_HPKE_KEY));
222}
223
224void EVP_HPKE_KEY_cleanup(EVP_HPKE_KEY *key) {
225 // Nothing to clean up for now, but we may introduce a cleanup process in the
226 // future.
227}
228
229int EVP_HPKE_KEY_init(EVP_HPKE_KEY *key, const EVP_HPKE_KEM *kem,
230 const uint8_t *priv_key, size_t priv_key_len) {
231 EVP_HPKE_KEY_zero(key);
232 key->kem = kem;
233 if (!kem->init_key(key, kem, priv_key, priv_key_len)) {
234 key->kem = NULL;
235 return 0;
236 }
237 return 1;
238}
239
240int EVP_HPKE_KEY_public_key(const EVP_HPKE_KEY *key, uint8_t *out,
241 size_t *out_len, size_t max_out) {
242 if (max_out < key->kem->public_key_len) {
243 OPENSSL_PUT_ERROR(EVP, EVP_R_INVALID_BUFFER_SIZE);
244 return 0;
245 }
246 OPENSSL_memcpy(out, key->public_key, key->kem->public_key_len);
247 *out_len = key->kem->public_key_len;
248 return 1;
249}

282// HPKE implementation.
283
284// This is strlen("HPKE") + 3 * sizeof(uint16_t).
285#define HPKE_SUITE_ID_LEN 10
286
287// The suite_id for non-KEM pieces of HPKE is defined as concat("HPKE",
288// I2OSP(kem_id, 2), I2OSP(kdf_id, 2), I2OSP(aead_id, 2)).
289static int hpke_build_suite_id(const EVP_HPKE_CTX *ctx,
290 uint8_t out[HPKE_SUITE_ID_LEN]) {
291 CBB cbb;
292 int ret = CBB_init_fixed(&cbb, out, HPKE_SUITE_ID_LEN) &&
293 add_label_string(&cbb, "HPKE") &&
294 CBB_add_u16(&cbb, EVP_HPKE_DHKEM_X25519_HKDF_SHA256) &&
295 CBB_add_u16(&cbb, ctx->kdf->id) &&
296 CBB_add_u16(&cbb, ctx->aead->id);
297 CBB_cleanup(&cbb);
298 return ret;
299}
300
301#define HPKE_MODE_BASE 0
302
303static int hpke_key_schedule(EVP_HPKE_CTX *ctx, const uint8_t *shared_secret,
304 size_t shared_secret_len, const uint8_t *info,
305 size_t info_len) {
306 uint8_t suite_id[HPKE_SUITE_ID_LEN];
307 if (!hpke_build_suite_id(ctx, suite_id)) {
308 return 0;
309 }
310
311 // psk_id_hash = LabeledExtract("", "psk_id_hash", psk_id)
312 // TODO(davidben): Precompute this value and store it with the EVP_HPKE_KDF.
313 const EVP_MD *hkdf_md = ctx->kdf->hkdf_md_func();
314 uint8_t psk_id_hash[EVP_MAX_MD_SIZE];
315 size_t psk_id_hash_len;
316 if (!hpke_labeled_extract(hkdf_md, psk_id_hash, &psk_id_hash_len, NULL, 0,
317 suite_id, sizeof(suite_id), "psk_id_hash", NULL,
318 0)) {
319 return 0;
320 }
321
322 // info_hash = LabeledExtract("", "info_hash", info)
323 uint8_t info_hash[EVP_MAX_MD_SIZE];
324 size_t info_hash_len;
325 if (!hpke_labeled_extract(hkdf_md, info_hash, &info_hash_len, NULL, 0,
326 suite_id, sizeof(suite_id), "info_hash", info,
327 info_len)) {
328 return 0;
329 }
330
331 // key_schedule_context = concat(mode, psk_id_hash, info_hash)
332 uint8_t context[sizeof(uint8_t) + 2 * EVP_MAX_MD_SIZE];
333 size_t context_len;
334 CBB context_cbb;
335 if (!CBB_init_fixed(&context_cbb, context, sizeof(context)) ||
336 !CBB_add_u8(&context_cbb, HPKE_MODE_BASE) ||
337 !CBB_add_bytes(&context_cbb, psk_id_hash, psk_id_hash_len) ||
338 !CBB_add_bytes(&context_cbb, info_hash, info_hash_len) ||
339 !CBB_finish(&context_cbb, NULL, &context_len)) {
340 return 0;
341 }
342
343 // secret = LabeledExtract(shared_secret, "secret", psk)
344 uint8_t secret[EVP_MAX_MD_SIZE];
345 size_t secret_len;
346 if (!hpke_labeled_extract(hkdf_md, secret, &secret_len, shared_secret,
347 shared_secret_len, suite_id, sizeof(suite_id),
348 "secret", NULL, 0)) {
349 return 0;
350 }
351
352 // key = LabeledExpand(secret, "key", key_schedule_context, Nk)
353 const EVP_AEAD *aead = ctx->aead->aead_func();
354 uint8_t key[EVP_AEAD_MAX_KEY_LENGTH];
355 const size_t kKeyLen = EVP_AEAD_key_length(aead);
356 if (!hpke_labeled_expand(hkdf_md, key, kKeyLen, secret, secret_len, suite_id,
357 sizeof(suite_id), "key", context, context_len) ||
358 !EVP_AEAD_CTX_init(&ctx->aead_ctx, aead, key, kKeyLen,
359 EVP_AEAD_DEFAULT_TAG_LENGTH, NULL)) {
360 return 0;
361 }
362
363 // base_nonce = LabeledExpand(secret, "base_nonce", key_schedule_context, Nn)
364 if (!hpke_labeled_expand(hkdf_md, ctx->base_nonce,
365 EVP_AEAD_nonce_length(aead), secret, secret_len,
366 suite_id, sizeof(suite_id), "base_nonce", context,
367 context_len)) {
368 return 0;
369 }
370
371 // exporter_secret = LabeledExpand(secret, "exp", key_schedule_context, Nh)
372 if (!hpke_labeled_expand(hkdf_md, ctx->exporter_secret, EVP_MD_size(hkdf_md),
373 secret, secret_len, suite_id, sizeof(suite_id),
374 "exp", context, context_len)) {
375 return 0;
376 }
377
378 return 1;
379}

382 OPENSSL_memset(ctx, 0, sizeof(EVP_HPKE_CTX));
383 EVP_AEAD_CTX_zero(&ctx->aead_ctx);
384}

388}
389
390int EVP_HPKE_CTX_setup_sender(EVP_HPKE_CTX *ctx, uint8_t *out_enc,
391 size_t *out_enc_len, size_t max_enc,
392 const EVP_HPKE_KEM *kem, const EVP_HPKE_KDF *kdf,
393 const EVP_HPKE_AEAD *aead,
394 const uint8_t *peer_public_key,
395 size_t peer_public_key_len, const uint8_t *info,
396 size_t info_len) {
397 uint8_t seed[MAX_SEED_LEN];
398 RAND_bytes(seed, kem->seed_len);
399 return EVP_HPKE_CTX_setup_sender_with_seed_for_testing(
400 ctx, out_enc, out_enc_len, max_enc, kem, kdf, aead, peer_public_key,
401 peer_public_key_len, info, info_len, seed, kem->seed_len);
402}
403
404int EVP_HPKE_CTX_setup_sender_with_seed_for_testing(
405 EVP_HPKE_CTX *ctx, uint8_t *out_enc, size_t *out_enc_len, size_t max_enc,
406 const EVP_HPKE_KEM *kem, const EVP_HPKE_KDF *kdf, const EVP_HPKE_AEAD *aead,
407 const uint8_t *peer_public_key, size_t peer_public_key_len,
408 const uint8_t *info, size_t info_len, const uint8_t *seed,
409 size_t seed_len) {
410 EVP_HPKE_CTX_zero(ctx);
411 ctx->is_sender = 1;
412 ctx->kdf = kdf;
413 ctx->aead = aead;
414 uint8_t shared_secret[MAX_SHARED_SECRET_LEN];
415 size_t shared_secret_len;
416 if (!kem->encap_with_seed(kem, shared_secret, &shared_secret_len, out_enc,
417 out_enc_len, max_enc, peer_public_key,
418 peer_public_key_len, seed, seed_len) ||
419 !hpke_key_schedule(ctx, shared_secret, shared_secret_len, info,
420 info_len)) {
421 EVP_HPKE_CTX_cleanup(ctx);
422 return 0;
423 }
424 return 1;
425}
426
427int EVP_HPKE_CTX_setup_recipient(EVP_HPKE_CTX *ctx, const EVP_HPKE_KEY *key,
428 const EVP_HPKE_KDF *kdf,
429 const EVP_HPKE_AEAD *aead, const uint8_t *enc,
430 size_t enc_len, const uint8_t *info,
431 size_t info_len) {
432 EVP_HPKE_CTX_zero(ctx);
433 ctx->is_sender = 0;
434 ctx->kdf = kdf;
435 ctx->aead = aead;
436 uint8_t shared_secret[MAX_SHARED_SECRET_LEN];
437 size_t shared_secret_len;
438 if (!key->kem->decap(key, shared_secret, &shared_secret_len, enc, enc_len) ||
439 !hpke_key_schedule(ctx, shared_secret, sizeof(shared_secret), info,
440 info_len)) {
441 EVP_HPKE_CTX_cleanup(ctx);
442 return 0;
443 }
444 return 1;
445}
446
447static void hpke_nonce(const EVP_HPKE_CTX *ctx, uint8_t *out_nonce,
448 size_t nonce_len) {
449 assert(nonce_len >= 8);
450
451 // Write padded big-endian bytes of |ctx->seq| to |out_nonce|.
452 OPENSSL_memset(out_nonce, 0, nonce_len);
453 uint64_t seq_copy = ctx->seq;
454 for (size_t i = 0; i < 8; i++) {
455 out_nonce[nonce_len - i - 1] = seq_copy & 0xff;
456 seq_copy >>= 8;
457 }
458
459 // XOR the encoded sequence with the |ctx->base_nonce|.
460 for (size_t i = 0; i < nonce_len; i++) {
461 out_nonce[i] ^= ctx->base_nonce[i];
462 }
463}
464
465int EVP_HPKE_CTX_open(EVP_HPKE_CTX *ctx, uint8_t *out, size_t *out_len,
466 size_t max_out_len, const uint8_t *in, size_t in_len,
467 const uint8_t *ad, size_t ad_len) {
468 if (ctx->is_sender) {
469 OPENSSL_PUT_ERROR(EVP, ERR_R_SHOULD_NOT_HAVE_BEEN_CALLED);
470 return 0;
471 }
472 if (ctx->seq == UINT64_MAX) {
473 OPENSSL_PUT_ERROR(EVP, ERR_R_OVERFLOW);
474 return 0;
475 }
476
477 uint8_t nonce[EVP_AEAD_MAX_NONCE_LENGTH];
478 const size_t nonce_len = EVP_AEAD_nonce_length(ctx->aead_ctx.aead);
479 hpke_nonce(ctx, nonce, nonce_len);
480
481 if (!EVP_AEAD_CTX_open(&ctx->aead_ctx, out, out_len, max_out_len, nonce,
482 nonce_len, in, in_len, ad, ad_len)) {
483 return 0;
484 }
485 ctx->seq++;
486 return 1;
487}
488
489int EVP_HPKE_CTX_seal(EVP_HPKE_CTX *ctx, uint8_t *out, size_t *out_len,
490 size_t max_out_len, const uint8_t *in, size_t in_len,
491 const uint8_t *ad, size_t ad_len) {
492 if (!ctx->is_sender) {
493 OPENSSL_PUT_ERROR(EVP, ERR_R_SHOULD_NOT_HAVE_BEEN_CALLED);
494 return 0;
495 }
496 if (ctx->seq == UINT64_MAX) {
497 OPENSSL_PUT_ERROR(EVP, ERR_R_OVERFLOW);
498 return 0;
499 }
500
501 uint8_t nonce[EVP_AEAD_MAX_NONCE_LENGTH];
502 const size_t nonce_len = EVP_AEAD_nonce_length(ctx->aead_ctx.aead);
503 hpke_nonce(ctx, nonce, nonce_len);
504
505 if (!EVP_AEAD_CTX_seal(&ctx->aead_ctx, out, out_len, max_out_len, nonce,
506 nonce_len, in, in_len, ad, ad_len)) {
507 return 0;
508 }
509 ctx->seq++;
510 return 1;
511}
512
513int EVP_HPKE_CTX_export(const EVP_HPKE_CTX *ctx, uint8_t *out,
514 size_t secret_len, const uint8_t *context,
515 size_t context_len) {
516 uint8_t suite_id[HPKE_SUITE_ID_LEN];
517 if (!hpke_build_suite_id(ctx, suite_id)) {
518 return 0;
519 }
520 const EVP_MD *hkdf_md = ctx->kdf->hkdf_md_func();
521 if (!hpke_labeled_expand(hkdf_md, out, secret_len, ctx->exporter_secret,
522 EVP_MD_size(hkdf_md), suite_id, sizeof(suite_id),
523 "sec", context, context_len)) {
524 return 0;
525 }
526 return 1;
527}

529size_t EVP_HPKE_CTX_max_overhead(const EVP_HPKE_CTX *ctx) {
530 assert(ctx->is_sender);
531 return EVP_AEAD_max_overhead(EVP_AEAD_CTX_aead(&ctx->aead_ctx));
532}
